| # | Severity | OWASP Category | Issue |
|---|----------|----------------|-------|
| 1 | 🔴 HIGH | A03 – Injection | No input validation/sanitization |
| 2 | 🔴 HIGH | A05 – Misconfiguration | No security headers |
| 3 | 🔴 HIGH | A01 – Broken Access Control | No authentication/authorization |
| 4 | 🟡 MED | A04 – Insecure Design | No rate limiting |
| 5 | 🟡 MED | A04 – Insecure Design | No body parser size limits |
| 6 | 🟡 MED | A01/A03 | PII exposure in response |
| 7 | 🟡 MED | A05 – Misconfiguration | No CORS configuration |
| 8 | 🟢 LOW | A05 – Misconfiguration | No error handling (stack trace leak) |
| 9 | 🟢 LOW | — | Hardcoded port |

**Minimum recommended packages to add:** `helmet`, `express-rate-limit`, `cors`, `express-validator`, and a JWT library (e.g., `jsonwebtoken`) for auth.

