Without explicit CORS configuration, browser behavior defaults apply. Once a frontend is added, this will either be too open or require ad-hoc fixes.

**Recommendation:** Configure CORS explicitly.

```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS?.split(',') || 'https://yourdomain.com',
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
  credentials: true,
}));
```

---

## 🟠 MEDIUM — No Error Handling (OWASP A09: Security Logging & Monitoring Failures)

There is no global error handler. Unhandled errors will leak Express stack traces to clients, revealing internal paths and dependencies.

**Recommendation:** Add a global error handler.

